  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Intelligent Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>:</p><ul><li>Develop, maintain, and optimize Tableau dashboards and reports based on business requirements.          </li><li>Assist in data preparation, blending, and transformation for visualization.          </li><li>Work with stakeholders to gather requirements and translate them into effective visualizations.  </li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to dashboards, data sources, and performance.        </li><li>Ensure dashboards follow best practices for usability, performance, and design.          </li><li>Collaborate with data engineers and analysts to integrate data from various sources (SQL, Excel, APIs, etc.).     </li><li>Document dashboard designs, data flows, and development processes.        </li><li>Stay updated with the latest Tableau features and BI trends.  </li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Skills</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Education</strong>: Polytechnic Diploma or bachelor’s degree in computer science, Data Analytics, Business, or a related field (or equivalent experience).  </li></ul><p><strong>Experience</strong>:        </p><ul><li>0–2 years of experience with Tableau Desktop (certification is a plus).      </li><li>Basic understanding of data visualization principles and dashboard design.         </li><li>Familiarity with SQL for data querying and manipulation.         </li><li>Exposure to data modelling, ETL processes, or BI tools is a bonus.  </li></ul><p><strong>Technical</strong> <strong>Skills</strong>:        </p><ul><li>Proficiency in Tableau (calculations, parameters, LOD expressions).        </li><li>Basic knowledge of data warehousing concepts.     </li><li>Experience with Excel or other data analysis tools.  </li></ul><p><strong>Soft Skills</strong>:          </p><ul><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.           </li><li>Good communication skills to collaborate with non-technical teams.          </li><li>Eagerness to learn and adapt in a fast-paced environment.  </li></ul>",
